SECTION 1 — SPACE AND LATTICE (RUBRIC CUBE)
-------------------------------------------
Ambient space: ℝ³. Lattice C = {−1,0,1}³ (27 cube centers).
Strata of lattice: body center, face centers (6), edge centers (12), corners (8).
Build stages: incremental sets C1..C4 adding centers, faces, corners, full lattice.

Ambient space: ℝ³ with Cartesian coordinates (x, y, z).

Discrete lattice of cube centers:
    C = { (x,y,z) | x,y,z ∈ {−1,0,1} }      |C| = 27

Strata:
    • Body center:        B = { (0,0,0) }
    • Face centers:       F = { (±1,0,0), (0,±1,0), (0,0,±1) }          (6)
    • Edge centers:       E_C = { exactly two coordinates ±1, one 0 }   (12)
    • Corners:            K = { (ε1,ε2,ε3) | εi ∈ {−1,+1} }             (8)

Build stages:
    C1 = B
    C2 = C1 ∪ F
    C3 = C2 ∪ K
    C4 = C = {−1,0,1}³

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 2 — GEOMETRY OF EACH CUBE
---------------------------------
Unit cubes (side s = 1); vertex generator V(c) and edge set E(c) for each cube 
centered at c ∈ C.

Side length: s = 1
Half-side:  h = 1/2

Vertex generator for cube centered at c ∈ C:
    V(c) = { c + (i h, j h, k h) | i,j,k ∈ {−1,+1} }

Edges of cube at c:
    E(c) = { [v,w] | v,w ∈ V(c), v and w differ in exactly one coordinate by s }

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 3 — LAYER PREDICATES (SID.INTERACTION)
----------------------------------------------
Boolean predicates to identify six layers (top, bottom, front, back, right,
left) based on coordinates; indicator form χ_layer.

Top layer:       L_top(p)      ⇔ p.z = +1
Bottom layer:    L_bottom(p)   ⇔ p.z = −1
Front layer:     L_front(p)    ⇔ p.y = +1
Back layer:      L_back(p)     ⇔ p.y = −1
Right layer:     L_right(p)    ⇔ p.x = +1
Left layer:      L_left(p)     ⇔ p.x = −1

Indicator form:
    χ_layer(p) = 1 if predicate true, else 0

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 4 — ROTATION OPERATORS (SID.DYNAMICS)
---------------------------------------------
Standard axis rotation matrices R_x, R_y, R_z.
Restricted rotations T_layer,axis(θ) apply an axis rotation only to points in
a chosen lattice layer, inducing permutations of the 27 centers. Defines group
G_layers ⊂ Sym(27).

Axis rotations (SO(3)):

R_x(θ) =
    [ 1      0        0     ]
    [ 0   cosθ   −sinθ ]
    [ 0   sinθ    cosθ ]

R_y(θ) =
    [ cosθ   0   sinθ ]
    [ 0      1     0  ]
    [ −sinθ  0   cosθ ]

R_z(θ) =
    [ cosθ  −sinθ   0 ]
    [ sinθ   cosθ   0 ]
    [ 0        0    1 ]

Restricted layer rotation:
    T_layer,axis(θ)(p) =
        if L_layer(p) then R_axis(θ) p
        else p

Permutation action:
    Each T_layer,axis(θ) induces a bijection on C.
    Group of all layer moves:
        G_layers ⊂ Sym(27)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 5 — TIME-DEPENDENT DYNAMICS (PED.DYNAMICS)
--------------------------------------------------
Time parameter t ∈ [0,T]; C_active(t) evolves through build stages.
Layer moves are animated by time ramps θ_i(t) from 0 → target angles (±π/2, ±π, ...).
Global orbit (continuous rotation) R_global(t) can be composed with layer moves.

Normalized time: t ∈ [0, T]

Build phase:
    C_active(t) transitions through {C1, C2, C3, C4}

Layer moves:
    For move i:
        θ_i(t) ramps from 0 → target angle (±π/2, ±π, ...)
        Apply T_layer_i(θ_i(t)) to centers and vertices

Global orbit:
    φ(t) = ω t + φ0
    R_global(t) = R_y(φ(t)) or composition with R_x, R_z

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 6 — PROJECTION (PED.EVALUATION)
---------------------------------------
Perspective projection formula (with focal factor f and offset d) and 
orthographic projection (X,Y).

Perspective projection:
    Given rotated point (X,Y,Z):
        (x_s, y_s) = f * ( X/(Z+d),  Y/(Z+d) )

Orthographic projection:
        (x_s, y_s) = (X, Y)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SECTION 7 — RENDERING
---------------------
Wireframe rendering rules: neon green emissive edges on black background; 
active cubes/vertices/edges determined by C_active(t) and transformed geometry.

Wireframe only:
    • Neon green emissive edges
    • Black background
    • Active cubes: C_active(t)
    • Active vertices: V_active(t) = ⋃_{c ∈ C_active(t)} V(c after transforms)
    • Active edges:    E_active(t) = ⋃_{c ∈ C_active(t)} E(c after transforms)

