SECTION 8 — CONWAY POLYHEDRON NOTATION
================================================================================
Quick reference: seeds (T,O,C,I,D, Pn, etc.) and operators (d, t, a, e, k, j, 
g, s, b, o, m, r, p).

Operator composition is right-to-left; key identities listed (aa = e, da = j, 
d^2 = identity).

Examples for cube seed (C → dC, tC, aC, eC, kC, jC, taC, gtC).

Conway notation describes convex polyhedra using:
    • Seeds (capital letters)
    • Operators (lowercase letters)

Operators apply right-to-left:
    op_k ... op_2 op_1 Seed

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SEEDS (CAPITAL LETTERS)
-----------------------
Platonic solids:
    T   = Tetrahedron
    O   = Octahedron
    C   = Cube
    I   = Icosahedron
    D   = Dodecahedron

Other seeds:
    Pn  = n-gonal prism
    An  = n-gonal antiprism
    Yn  = n-gonal pyramid
    Jn  = Johnson solid n
    H   = Hexagonal tiling

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

OPERATORS (LOWERCASE LETTERS)
-----------------------------
Primary operators:
    d   = Dual
    t   = Truncate
    a   = Ambo / Rectify
    e   = Expand / Cantellate
    k   = Kis
    j   = Join (j = da)
    g   = Gyro
    s   = Snub
    b   = Bevel (b = ta)
    o   = Ortho (o = de)

Extended:
    m   = Meta
    r   = Reflect
    p   = Propeller

Identities:
    aa = e
    da = j
    d^2 = identity

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLES USING CUBE SEED (C)
----------------------------
C       = Cube
dC      = Octahedron
tC      = Truncated cube
aC      = Cuboctahedron
eC      = Rhombicuboctahedron
kC      = Tetrakis hexahedron
jC      = Rhombic dodecahedron
taC     = Truncated cuboctahedron
gtC     = Gyro-truncated cube

