SECTION 9 — RUBRIC CUBE × CONWAY MAPPING
----------------------------------------
Mapping: Rubric Cube ↔ Conway operators
Intuitive correspondences:

 a (rectify / ambo): related to moving toward edge midpoints / layer rotations
 t (truncate): removing corners
 e (expand): displacing face centers outward
 k (kis): extruding pyramids from faces
 d (dual): swaps face-center and corner roles

Claim: the Rubric Cube lattice can serve as a discrete geometric substrate to 
model Conway operator actions and enable RDG-style (render-dynamics-geometry)
evaluation.

Rubric Cube lattice:
    L = {−1,0,1}³   (27 centers)

Mapping to Conway operators:
    • Rectification (a):
        resembles rotating layers to edge midpoints.
    • Truncation (t):
        resembles removing corner nodes (±1,±1,±1).
    • Expansion (e):
        resembles outward displacement of face centers.
    • Kis (k):
        resembles adding pyramids on faces (face-center extrusion).
    • Dual (d):
        swaps face centers ↔ corner centers.

Thus the Rubric Cube lattice provides a discrete geometric substrate for
Conway operator actions, enabling RDG-style operator evaluation.

